plough camp
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a travelling horse-drawn camp in which itinerant contract ploughmen and their ancillary staff lived. [Originally consisting of tents, then later cookhouse hut and sleeping quarters were drawn on sled or wheels.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
